item.title: CVE-2018-3922|2024-09-17T02:01:21.480Z -- computerinsel -- computerinsel%20photoline
item.description: A memory corruption vulnerability exists in the ANI-parsing functionality of Computerinsel Photoline 20.54. A specially crafted ANI image processed via the application can lead to a stack overflow, overwriting arbitrary data. An attacker can deliver an ANI image to trigger this vulnerability and gain code execution.

item.title: CVE-2017-12107|2024-09-17T00:26:01.151Z -- computerinsel -- photoline
item.description: An memory corruption vulnerability exists in the .PCX parsing functionality of Computerinsel Photoline 20.02. A specially crafted .PCX file can cause a vulnerability resulting in potential code execution. An attacker can send a specific .PCX file to trigger this vulnerability.
